<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-300-738  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 300 738.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telecommunications  March 1990 v24 n3 p15(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New Congressional study warns US may foreclose policy options.andO;(government policy and communications infrastructure development)(Global News)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Valovic, Thomas S.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US Congress's Office of Technological Assessment (OTA)released a report entitled 'Critical Connections: Communicationsfor the Future' which presents the results of a two-year study ongovernment policy and the communications industry.andP;  The reportcriticizes the disorganized and fragmented approach of USgovernment policy toward the development of the infrastructure fordata transmission and communications networks.andP;  Without a moreorganized policy in such areas as security, public networks andother communications technology, use of telecommunications ininternational commerce, and equal access to information,significant class differences in access to knowledge may result.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Office of Technology AssessmentOutlookGovernmentPolicyCommunications IndustryReports.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>